# What is LcdProgressBar?
LcdProgressBar is an Arduino library for displaying a progress bar in LCD display.

# Dependencies
The LCD display must be previously initialized. This library uses LiquidCrystal library for displaying.

# Expected result
![LcdProgressBar Demo](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/wloche/LcdProgressBar/master/extras/LcdProgressBar-2s.gif)

:movie_camera: [Video on Youtube](https://youtu.be/3SRARTk7fZY)

# Example
:information_source: Refer to full example: [examples/Timer/Timer.ino](https://github.com/wloche/LcdProgressBar/blob/master/examples/Timer/Timer.ino), Breadboard and electronic [schema here](https://github.com/wloche/LcdProgressBar/wiki/LcdProgressBar-Electronic-schemas).

What you need is extracted bellow.

## includes
```c++
#include <LiquidCrystal.h>
#include <LcdProgressBar.h> //## Include this lib
```

## Initializations
```c++
LiquidCrystal lcd(12, 11, 5, 4, 3, 2);
LcdProgressBar lpg(&lcd, 1, 16);
```

## Initializing the progress bar
```c++
void initLpg()
{
  //-- start time
  startedMillis = millis();

  //-- Set min and max values
  lpg.setMinValue(startedMillis);
  lpg.setMaxValue(startedMillis + duration);
}
```

## Drawing the progress bar
```c++
  //-- draw progress bar
  lpg.draw(currentMillis);
```

or via the alias `drawValue` (the [LcdBarGraph](https://github.com/prampec/LcdBarGraph) way :wink:):
```c++
  //-- draw progress bar
  lpg.drawValue(currentMillis);
```

